3 payments, and the usual ordinary expenses of the local board for the interval between the
4 beginning of the budget year and the adoption of the budget. Interim appropriations so made shall
5 be charged to the proper appropriations in the adopted budget.
6 (j) Finance Officer. – Except as otherwise provided, the local board shall designate (i) a
7 part-time or full-time employee of the board other than the general manager or (ii) the The finance
8 officer of the appointing authority with consent of the appointing authority to be shall be the
9 finance officer for the local board. The Commission, for good cause shown, may grant a waiver
10 to allow the general manager of a board also to be the finance officer. Good cause includes, but
11 is not limited to, the fact that the board operates no more than two stores, and any approval for
12 the general manager also to be the finance officer shall apply until the board operates more than
