1 of working capital, investments, appointment of a budget officer, appointment of a financial
2 officer, daily deposit of funds, bonding of employees, auditing of operations, and the schedule,
3 manner and other procedures for distribution of profits. The Commission may also adopt any
4 other rules concerning the financial operations of local boards which are needed to assure the
5 proper accountability of public funds. The Commission may vary these rules and regulations
6 according to any other criteria reasonably related to the purpose or complexity of the financial
