4 liquor. A permittee shall designate and maintain at least ten percent (10%) of
5 the permittee's guest rooms as rooms that do not have a guest room cabinet. A
6 permittee may dispense alcoholic beverages from a guest room cabinet only
7 in accordance with written policies and procedures filed with and approved
8 by the Commission. A permittee shall provide a reasonable number of vending
9 machines, coolers, or similar machines on premises for the sale of soft drinks
10 to hotel guests.
11 A guest room cabinet permit may be issued to any of the following:
